FBIS4-62429 "drsov094_e_94004" FBIS-SOV-94-094 Daily Report 13 May 1994 UKRAINE International Affairs Military Conversion Agreement Signed in Washington Military Conversion Agreement Signed in Washington LD1305164594 Kiev UNIAR in Ukrainian 1100 GMT 13 May 94 LD1305164594 Kiev UNIAR Ukrainian BFN [Text] Washington, 13 May. An agreement in the sphere of military conversion was signed during the visit by Deputy Prime Minister Valeriy Shmarov to the United States. US Defense Secretary William Perry described the document, which is first in the history of Kiev-Washington relations, as a historic one. The agreement foresees a joint venture between the American company Westinghouse and Khartron production association in Kharkov. The Ukrainian-American enterprise will develop and produce high technology control systems for all types of electric power stations.
